```
lemma nat_log_le_real_logb {a b : ℕ} (_ : 0 < a)  : Nat.log b a ≤ Real.logb b a
```

and remove some `(hb : 1 < b)`  not needed hypotheses in previous lemmas

Thanks!
This is true for `b = 0` and for `b = 1`. Please see if `1 < b` can be dropped in some of the previous lemmas.
Done. Please have a look

```suggestion
  · have hb1' : 1 < (b : ℝ) := Nat.one_lt_cast.mpr hb
    apply le_antisymm
    · rw [← Int.zpow_le_iff_le_log hb hr, ← rpow_intCast b]
      refine le_of_le_of_eq ?_ (rpow_logb (zero_lt_one.trans hb1') hb1'.ne' hr)
      exact rpow_le_rpow_of_exponent_le hb1'.le (Int.floor_le _)
    · rw [Int.le_floor, le_logb_iff_rpow_le hb1' hr, rpow_intCast]
      exact Int.zpow_log_le_self hb hr
```

```suggestion
  · rw [Nat.one_lt_iff_ne_zero_and_ne_one, ← or_iff_not_and_not] at hb
```

```suggestion
    cases hb
    · simp_all only [CharP.cast_eq_zero, logb_zero_left, Int.floor_zero, Int.log_zero_base]
    · simp_all only [Nat.cast_one, logb_one_left, Int.floor_zero, Int.log_one_base]
```

```suggestion
  · rw [Nat.one_lt_iff_ne_zero_and_ne_one, ← or_iff_not_and_not] at hb
    cases hb
    · simp_all only [CharP.cast_eq_zero, logb_zero_left, Int.ceil_zero, Int.clog_zero_left]
    · simp_all only [Nat.cast_one, logb_one_left, Int.ceil_zero, Int.clog_one_left]
```

```suggestion
theorem log_zero_base (r : R) : log 0 r = 0 := by
  simp only [log, Nat.log_zero_left, Nat.cast_zero, Nat.clog_zero_left, neg_zero, ite_self]
```
Are there any other lemmas that use `base` in the name? Otherwise `left` is probably better
I changed it to `left`

```suggestion
theorem clog_one_left (r : R) : clog 1 r = 0 := by
  simp only [clog, Nat.log_one_left, Nat.cast_zero, Nat.clog_one_left, neg_zero, ite_self]
```

AFAICT, we use `typeFunction` for lemmas about `Type.function` that live in another namespace.
```suggestion
lemma natLog_le_logb (a b : ℕ) : Nat.log b a ≤ Real.logb b a := by
```

BTW, do we have `Nat.log b a = ⌊Real.logb b a⌋₊`?

Thanks!
bors d+
